Before joining music, Sheddy Empire were hustlers in Nairobi. They have a new song titled Shika Mandom, talking about what goes on in ghettos. "Hii ngoma ni real, yaani zile vitu zinahappen kwa mtaa about the hustle. We are one year old now since we started working together." Talking of cartels who asks for money to play their music, they said: "Cartels will always be there but what artistes need to do is to keep pushing your music." Sheddy Empire also addressed the controversy stirred by Timmy Tdat, when he pulled a woman's skirt up on stage. They said: "Vile Timmy alifanya kwa stage si poa. Anafaa arespect wasichana bana. Have respect for women ata kama you are a big artiste."